// Rule ids whose dedicated `InvalidFiles/sbol-NNNNN.xml` corpus fixture the
// validator does not reject as an *error* under the all-flags-on config. Every
// machine-checkable rule additionally has a hermetic, firing negative fixture
// in `tests/rule_cases/`; this list tracks only the downloaded corpus fixtures
// that the strict error-match does not cover, and why. Each entry is one of:
//
//   - SHOULD-level best practice: the rule runs but emits at warning severity,
//     so the corpus fixture is not an error-match. The conformance suite
//     asserts these against the SBOL2_bp corpus as warnings. Covers 10302,
//     10407, 10511, 10518, 10520, 10523, 10525, 10527, 10528, 10529, 10706,
//     10707, 10711, 10712, 10903, 11412, 11507, 11511, 11905, 11907, 12007,
//     12408, 12909, 12910, 12911, 12912, 12913, 13006, 13018, 13019, 13020,
//     13021, 13022, 13206, 13505.
//
//   - MachineUncheckable (▲): the rule requires cross-document resolution and
//     is catalogued MachineUncheckable, so it never emits. Covers the MapsTo
//     remote-resolution rules 10808, 10809, 10811 and the cross-document
//     CombinatorialDerivation rules 12908, 13005, 13011, 13016, 13017.
//
//   - Reader-scope: 10106 requires the reader to retain declared XML namespace
//     bindings (discarded after parsing); 12301 and 12303 require the reader to
//     synthesize a GenericTopLevel from an unknown SBOL-namespace top-level
//     type. These are reader changes outside the validator's scope.
//
//   - Corpus nuance: 10307 (the corpus fixture's attachment reference is not
//     the local-completeness shape the validator rejects) and 13012 (the corpus
//     fixture exercises the cross-document variantDerivation portion). Both
//     have firing hermetic negatives in `tests/rule_cases/`.
//
// Kept explicit so the strict/loose match set is auditable and shrinks as
// reader and resolver support grows.
[
    "sbol2-10106",
    "sbol2-10302",
    "sbol2-10307",
    "sbol2-10407",
    "sbol2-10511",
    "sbol2-10518",
    "sbol2-10520",
    "sbol2-10523",
    "sbol2-10525",
    "sbol2-10527",
